In old English
law. A great or general reap-day. Cowell;
Blount.

MAISON DE DIEU. Fr. A hospital;
an almshouse; a monastery. St. 39 Eliz. c.
5. Literally, “house of God.”

MARQUIS, or MARQUESS. In English
law. One of the second order of nobility;
next in order to a duke.

In old Scotch law. A maire;
an officer or executor of summons. Otherwise called "preco regis." Skene.

| MASAGIUM,. L. Lat. A messuage.

(Corruption of maison
de Dieu.) A house of God; a monastery;
religious house or hospital. See 39 Eliz. c. 5.

In old English law. Mere;
naked or abstract. Mecrum fus, mere right.
Bract. fol. 31.

